The U.S. reported a record 1 million new coronavirus cases on Monday, according to data from Johns Hopkins University. It is the highest single-day total reported cases from any country during the pandemic. The U.S. has been criticizing China's zero-COVID strategy, but its own response has led to the deaths of 830,000 people. So which country cares more about human rights of the ordinary people? In this episode of BizBeat, CGTN's Guan Xin believes the facts are self-explanatory.